title: Labour’s Tom Watson branded ‘utterly embarrassing’ after performing ‘dab’ during PMQs
text:
Twitter users were quick to spot the Labour MP’s apparent ‘dab’, with Gareth Gaston posting: “Utterly embarrassing when a 50 year old man dabs during #PMQs.” 
Charlie Ford wrote: “Tom Watson dabbing in PMQs is the final nail in the coffin.” 
James Trench added: “The only consolation of the dab on #PMQs is Corbyn not having a clue what Tom Watson was doing”. PARLIAMENT.TV Labour deputy leader Tom Watson appeared to perform a 'dab' as Jeremy Corbyn sat down GETTY Premier League footballer Jesse Lingard perfoms a 'dab' after scoring for Manchester United Utterly embarrassing when a 50 year old man dabs during #PMQs Twitter user Gareth Gaston 
The ‘dab’ dance craze has been used by Premier League footballers such as Manchester United’s Jesse Lingard during goal celebrations. 
The stunt has been imported from the US, where American Football stars have previously performed a ‘dab’ during NFL games. Related articles
